From: Peios <kernel@peios.org>
Subject: FACS patch 15: execveat(AT_EMPTY_PATH) granted mask check

For fd-based exec, check FILE_EXECUTE in the original fd's granted
mask rather than re-opening the file. This makes exec part of the
handle model: an fd opened with FILE_EXECUTE carries SD
authorization for execution. SD changes after open do not affect
the granted mask.

STATUS: DEFERRED for v1. The current implementation uses a live
AccessCheck via the kernel's re-opened file in do_open_execat().
FILE_EXECUTE is in the legacy open compat set for regular files,
so the re-opened file gets FILE_EXECUTE if the SD allows it.
The functional difference is snapshot (patch 15) vs live (current):
SD changes between original open and exec would affect the live
check but not the snapshot. This is acceptable for v1.

Full implementation requires carrying the original struct file
reference through linux_binprm and checking it in bprm_check
before falling through to the re-opened file.
